<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <%= render "shared/page_header", title: "Help", size: "2xl" %>
  <%= render "shared/help_nav", current: :chatgpt_help %>

  <section class="pb-12">
    <h2 class="text-lg/8 font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Use PodRead with ChatGPT</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm/6 text-mist-700 dark:text-mist-400">
      Turn articles into podcast episodes directly from <strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">ChatGPT</strong>.
      Just share a link or paste text and ask ChatGPT to create a podcast episode.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-6 text-sm/6 text-mist-700 dark:text-mist-400">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Getting Started</h3>

      <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal pl-5 space-y-3">
        <li>
          Go to <a href="https://chatgpt.com/gpts" class="text-mist-950 underline dark:text-white">chatgpt.com/gpts</a> and search for <strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">PodRead</strong>, or open it directly: <a href="https://chatgpt.com/g/g-69c9d3dfbb8c819197e538a7a383ee38-podread" class="text-mist-950 underline dark:text-white">PodRead GPT</a>. Requires a ChatGPT Plus or Team plan.
        </li>
        <li>
          Try a prompt like <em>"Summarize this chat in a narrative optimized for text to speech and then turn it into a podcast."</em>
        </li>
        <li>
          The first time, ChatGPT will ask you to <strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">sign in to PodRead</strong>. Click the sign-in button, log in with your PodRead account, and click <strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Allow</strong> to authorize access.
        </li>
        <li>
          ChatGPT will send the desired text to PodRead. PodRead will convert the text to a podcast episode for your personal feed.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Example Prompts</h3>
      <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
        <pre class="rounded-lg bg-mist-50 dark:bg-mist-900 p-4 text-sm text-mist-950 dark:text-mist-200 overflow-x-auto"><code>Summarize this chat and turn it into a podcast episode</code></pre>

        <pre class="rounded-lg bg-mist-50 dark:bg-mist-900 p-4 text-sm text-mist-950 dark:text-mist-200 overflow-x-auto"><code>Create a podcast episode from this text: [paste your text]</code></pre>

        <pre class="rounded-lg bg-mist-50 dark:bg-mist-900 p-4 text-sm text-mist-950 dark:text-mist-200 overflow-x-auto"><code>Show me my recent PodRead episodes</code></pre>

        <pre class="rounded-lg bg-mist-50 dark:bg-mist-900 p-4 text-sm text-mist-950 dark:text-mist-200 overflow-x-auto"><code>What voices does PodRead have?</code></pre>

        <pre class="rounded-lg bg-mist-50 dark:bg-mist-900 p-4 text-sm text-mist-950 dark:text-mist-200 overflow-x-auto"><code>What's my PodRead feed URL so I can add it to my podcast app?</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">What You Can Do</h3>
      <p class="mt-3">The PodRead GPT can:</p>

      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
        <li><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Create episodes from URLs</strong> &mdash; paste any article link</li>
        <li><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Create episodes from text</strong> &mdash; paste content directly into the chat</li>
        <li><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">List your episodes</strong> &mdash; see what you've created recently</li>
        <li><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Check episode status</strong> &mdash; see if audio generation is finished</li>
        <li><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Delete episodes</strong> &mdash; remove episodes from your feed</li>
        <li><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Show available voices</strong> &mdash; see voice options (change your default in <a href="<%= settings_path %>" class="text-mist-950 underline dark:text-white">Settings</a>)</li>
        <li><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Get your feed URL</strong> &mdash; add to any podcast app to listen</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Troubleshooting</h3>

      <div class="mt-3 space-y-4">
        <div>
          <p class="font-medium text-mist-950 dark:text-white">ChatGPT says it can't connect to PodRead</p>
          <p class="mt-1">Try signing out and back in. In the ChatGPT conversation, click the PodRead sign-in prompt again to re-authorize.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-medium text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Want to disconnect?</p>
          <p class="mt-1">
            Go to your <a href="<%= settings_path %>" class="text-mist-950 underline dark:text-white">PodRead Settings</a> page and click "Disconnect" next to ChatGPT in the Connected Apps section.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-medium text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Episode limit reached?</p>
          <p class="mt-1">
            Free accounts can create <%= AppConfig::Tiers::FREE_MONTHLY_EPISODES %> episodes per month.
            <a href="<%= upgrade_path %>" class="text-mist-950 underline dark:text-white">Upgrade</a> for unlimited episodes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-medium text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Don't have a PodRead account?</p>
          <p class="mt-1">
            <a href="<%= root_path %>" class="text-mist-950 underline dark:text-white">Sign up at podread.app</a> first, then try the PodRead GPT again.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
